eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports has the details. #DStv403 #eNCA CAPE TOWN - Some elderly residents of Mamre just outside Cape Town claim they are being swindled out of their Sassa grants for a place to stay. They are paying over R1,300 to stay on the illegally occupied land, get food and make use of the ablution facilities. Their landlady is also occupying the land illegally. Civic organisation, the Mamre Residents Association, claims the elderly residents have been brought to the land under false pretences, and they urgently need help. The provincial social development department says it will be investigating the matter. Watch the video above for more details on this story.